      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOHO WASHINGTON (3) is a talented colt who made it two wins on the trot at this circuit when he led from this barrier and drew away to score by close to 12m. That saw him unbeaten at this circuit and distance. Draws to push forward again so can land the hat trick. FOR SIXES (1) did a good job to come from the back row for a 4.2m fourth last week after kicking off his career with back-to-back wins, both from tougher draws than this. Progressive and is well served by the inside barrier. GENERAL LINCOLN (4) is looming as a threat after another good effort last start, finishing a 1.2m second to give him two wins and two placings from his last five outings here. CANTPLZA MALTEEZA (2) has been coming from the back row and did well to score here two back so could be competitive from this more favourable draw.",
